# Environment Configuration

## Development Environment

Create a `.env` file in the frontend directory with the following configuration:

```env
# API Configuration
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000/api/v1

# Optional: Enable debug logging
VITE_DEBUG=true
```

## Production Environment

For production deployment, set:

```env
# Production API endpoint
VITE_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com/api/v1

# Optional: Disable debug logging
VITE_DEBUG=false
```

## Docker Configuration

If using Docker, pass environment variables:

```dockerfile
ENV VITE_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com/api/v1
```

Or at runtime:

```bash
docker run -e VITE_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com/api/v1 myapp
```

## API URL Requirements

The API endpoint must:
- Be accessible from the browser
- Support CORS requests from your frontend domain
- Implement the required endpoints
- Return valid JSON responses
- Handle all specified status codes

## Vercel Deployment

Set environment variables in Vercel dashboard:

```
VITE_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com/api/v1
```

## Netlify Deployment

Create `netlify.toml`:

```toml
[build]
  command = "npm run build"
  publish = "dist"

[build.environment]
  VITE_API_URL = "https://api.yourdomain.com/api/v1"
```

## AWS Amplify Deployment

Set in Amplify Console:

```
VITE_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com/api/v1
```

## Local Testing with Mock API

For development without a real backend:

```bash
npm install -g json-server

# Create db.json with mock data
# Run: json-server --watch db.json --port 3001
```

Then set:
```env
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3001/api/v1
```
